Package de.elo.ix.client.esearch.query

Enum SearchFieldE

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<SearchFieldE>
de.elo.ix.client.esearch.query.SearchFieldE
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<SearchFieldE>, java.lang.constant.Constable
public enum SearchFieldE
extends java.lang.Enum<SearchFieldE>
implements java.io.Serializable

Use this class of constants to define in which field should be searched.

For every option, allowed FieldTypeE is given which is also the fallback type if provided type is incorrect.

Since:
11.00.000.013

  • Enum Constant Details

    • INDEXFIELD

      public static final SearchFieldE INDEXFIELD

      Use this constant if a index field is searched.

      Submit name of indexfield by QueryFilter.docMaskLine

      Depending on type of the corresponding DocMaskLine (DocMaskLine.type, the corresponding FieldTypeE can be used.
      DocMaskLines of type DocMaskLineC.TYPE_RELATION can be used with FieldTypeE.tokenized or FieldTypeE.notTokenized to search for the short name (Sord.name of the related Sord), or FieldTypeE.guid to search for the GUID of the related Sord.
